Class ArraySequence<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ArraySequence<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Deque<E>, IndexList<E>, PositionList<E>, Sequence<E>

    public class ArraySequence<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Sequence<E>
    File: ArraySequence.java Realization of a sequence by means of an array, which is doubled when the size of the sequence exceeds the capacity of the array.
    See Also:
    Sequence, IndexOutOfBoundsException, BoundaryViolationException, InvalidPositionException, EmptyDequeException

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      ArraySequence()
      Creates the indexed array with initial capacity 16.
